<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="435" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="41.[121,1327,2226,3205]" pageId="41" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[123,478,2975,3008]" pageId="41" pageNumber="435">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Dark Mexican Broad-clawed Shrew has a very restricted and fragmented distribution in the Chiapan Highlands, with a 75% deforestation rate. It is found in a 100ha protected area, Reserva Ecologica Huitepec.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
